:"MLNPointFeature","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointFeature","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Related examples","anchor":"Related-examples"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"TODO: Clustering point data, learn how to initialize","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"clusters and add them to your map.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","title":"MapLibre","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"role":"symbol","title":"MLNAnnotationView","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object that corresponds to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. When an annotation’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"offscreen."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotationView"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNFeature":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNFeature","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNFeature","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNFeature"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNFeature"},{"type":"text","text":"  protocol is used to provide details about geographic features"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"contained in an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource"},{"type":"text","text":" object. Each concrete"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"subclass of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape"},{"type":"text","text":" in turn has a subclass that conforms to this protocol. A"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"feature object associates a shape with an optional identifier and attributes."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnfeature"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationImage":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationImage"},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for presenting point-based"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"annotations visually on a map view. Annotation image objects wrap "},{"code":"UIImage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects and may be recycled later and put into a reuse queue that is maintained"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by the map view."}],"type":"topic","title":"MLNAnnotationImage","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationimage","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationImage","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationImage"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointFeatureCluster":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPointFeatureCluster"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointFeatureCluster","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object associates a point shape (with an optional"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identifier and attributes) and represents a point cluster."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointfeaturecluster","title":"MLNPointFeatureCluster","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointFeatureCluster","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointFeature":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointFeature","title":"MLNPointFeature","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPointFeature","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointfeature","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointFeature"},{"type":"text","text":" object associates a point shape with an optional"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identifier and attributes."}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNCluster":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A protocol that feature subclasses (i.e. those already conforming to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNFeature","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol) conform to if they represent clusters."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCluster","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlncluster","title":"MLNCluster","fragments":[{"text":"MLNCluster","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"title":"MLNAnnotation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}]}}}